\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes mandatory rules of behavior governing the acceptable use of Elko County Information Technology (IT) resources.
 It defines authorized and prohibited user activities to protect County operations,
 information,
 personnel,
 and the public from security,
 legal,
 operational,
 and reputational risk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all users granted access to County IT resources,
 including employees,
 elected officials,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 interns,
 and volunteers .
 County IT resources include County-owned,
 County-managed,
 and County-provisioned systems and services,
 including endpoints,
 networks,
 applications,
 cloud services,
 accounts,
 and County data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director (LASO):

\series default
 Shall maintain this policy and serve as the final authority on acceptable-use determinations and exception approvals.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Human Resources (HR):

\series default
 Shall ensure user acknowledgments are executed prior to initial access and retained for a minimum of seven (7) years following separation of employment or contract termination in accordance with the Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule .
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads:

\series default
 Shall ensure all personnel under their supervision execute required acknowledgments prior to access provisioning and report security incidents or lost CJI-capable devices within one (1) hour of discovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Users:

\series default
 Shall comply with this policy as a condition of access to County IT resources and shall protect County assets from unauthorized access,
 loss,
 or misuse.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Compliance:

\series default
 Adherence to this policy is mandatory.
 Violations may result in access revocation,
 disciplinary action up to and including termination,
 contract remedies,
 and referral for civil or criminal enforcement under 
\series bold
NRS 205
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Universal Applicability
\series default
:
 The standards defined herein apply to the use of County IT resources at all times and in all locations,
 including but not limited to County facilities,
 remote work locations,
 and during official travel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions:

\series default
 Exceptions shall be documented,
 risk-assessed,
 time-bound (not to exceed 12 months),
 and approved in writing by the IT Director.
 Exceptions involving CJI shall not reduce CJIS-mandated requirements.
\end_layout

