\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1.
 Ownership and Consent to Monitoring
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
County Property
\series default
:
 All Information Technology resources,
 including hardware,
 software,
 and data created,
 stored,
 or transmitted upon them,
 remain the sole property of Elko County regardless of the physical location of the asset.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
No Expectation of Privacy
\series default
:
 Users shall have no reasonable expectation of privacy when using County IT resources.
 Use constitutes consent to monitoring,
 logging,
 and disclosure for operational,
 security,
 legal,
 and investigative purposes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
System Notification
\series default
:
 System use notification banners implementing 
\series bold
NIST SP 800-53 AC-8
\series default
 shall be displayed on County systems as specified in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 to provide continuous notice of monitoring consent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2.
 Identity and Credentials
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Credential Protection
\series default
:
 Users shall not share passwords,
 tokens,
 or access badges.
 Account sharing is strictly prohibited.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Workstation Security
\series default
:
 Users shall lock devices (Win+L) whenever left unattended,
 even for brief periods.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3.
 Acceptable Use Standards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Official Use
\series default
:
 County IT resources are provided to support the official business of Elko County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Incidental Personal Use
\series default
:
 Limited personal use is permissible only if it is brief,
 occurs during non-work time (breaks/lunch),
 incurs no cost to the County,
 and does not interfere with productivity or violate any other County policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4.
 Prohibited Activities Users shall not:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Install unauthorized software,
 disable security controls,
 or use anonymization tools to bypass network filters.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Input Confidential or Restricted County data (per Policy 1.11) into external Generative AI or public Large Language Models (LLMs).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Use County IT resources for political campaigning,
 lobbying,
 or personal commercial ventures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Access,
 store,
 or distribute harassing,
 discriminatory,
 or sexually explicit content.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5.
 Reporting Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Incidents
\series default
:
 Users shall report suspected security incidents to Information Operations immediately.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Lost CJI Assets
\series default
:
 Lost or stolen devices capable of accessing Criminal Justice Information (CJI) must be reported to the IT Director (LASO) no later than 
\series bold
one (1) hour
\series default
 after discovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
General Assets
\series default
:
 All other lost or stolen County devices shall be reported within 
\series bold
one (1) business day
\series default
 of discovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6.
 Acknowledgment Requirement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prerequisite
\series default
:
 All users shall execute the Acceptable Use Policy Acknowledgment (found in Appendix 6.08) prior to being granted access to County IT resources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Refreshes
\series default
:
 This acknowledgment shall be refreshed annually or upon significant updates to this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Refusal
\series default
:
 Refusal to sign shall result in the immediate denial or revocation of access to all IT resources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7.
 Additional Requirements for Privileged Users
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Users with elevated privileges (Tier L3 and above) shall use privileged accounts only for tasks requiring elevated access;
 routine activities shall be performed using standard accounts.
 Privileged access is contingent on maintaining required background screening and role-based training specified in Policy 1.07 and Policy 2.03 .
\end_layout

